                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–1049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Edgar</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-10T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 10, 1949—9 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 10—2:14 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>108. [For] Merchant and Butterworth. T. V. Soong here. He tells me on
                    Generalissimo’s order to find political, economic, military solution to preclude
                    Communist takeover. Asked my advice. Have stalled. You may decide immediate
                    return or request my instructions.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 108, repeated Nanking 98.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edgar</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
